26/05/2011
BELGRADE, Serbia -- EU foreign policy chief Catherine Ashton said on Wednesday (May 25th), on the eve of her visit to Belgrade, that dialogue between Serbia and Kosovo is crucial to removing obstacles on the road to potential EU membership.
She stressed that the talks should find practical solutions to people's daily life problems.
Ashton also reaffirmed the EU's commitment to the European perspective of the Western Balkans and stressed the importance of regional co-operation.
(Tanjug, Beta, RTS, B92 - 26/05/11)
